-- Southampton Ties 2-2 Against Fulham in Soccer’s Premier League
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2012-10-07T14:27:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-07/southampton-ties-2-2-against-fulham-in-soccer-s-premier-league.html
Jose Fonte scored twice as
Southampton tied 2-2 against Fulham to climb out of the
relegation positions in English soccer’s Premier League.  Fonte gave the Saints a fourth-minute lead at their St.
Mary’s Stadium, and got his second goal as the game headed into
injury time at the end of the match. Southampton’s Jos Hooiveld
deflected the ball into his own net on 70 minutes, with Kieran
Richardson getting Fulham’s other goal.  Southampton climbs one spot to 17th in the 20-team league,
while Fulham remains ninth.  In today’s other matches, Newcastle hosts Manchester
United, Tottenham plays Aston Villa, while Liverpool faces
Stoke.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
